In some cases it may be necessary to involveexternal specialists in making this evaluation.a) If required and depending on the importance of the outsourced process, a guideline regarding control criteria shall be given to the contractor at thetime of outsourcing.b) It may be convenient or even necessary to define some or all of the methods to be used for control of the outsourced processes ina contract between the company and the contractor. Care would also be taken so as not to inhibit the contractor from proposinginnovations to the outsourced process.c) In some situations, it might not be possible to verify the output from outsourced process by subsequent monitoring or measurement.In these cases, company shall ensure that the control over the outsourced process includes process validation.Ensuring control over outsourced process does not absolve the company of its responsibility of conformity to all customer, statutoryand regulatory requirements.The type and extent of control to be applied to the outsourced process can be influenced by factors such as:a) The potential impact of the outsourced process on the company’s capability to provide management services that conforms to thecustomers’ requirements. b) The degree to which the control for the process is shared.5.10ACCOUNTING CODES PERTAINING TO TECHNICAL DEPARTMENTLubricating oil -
